# Mobile modals must not be full-width

On mobile, **centered modals/dialogs** must keep horizontal inset — never edge-to-edge.

## Required width

```jsx
// ✅ GOOD — inset on mobile, capped on larger screens
<DialogContent className="w-[calc(100vw-1.5rem)] sm:max-w-md">

// ❌ BAD — stretches edge-to-edge on phones
<DialogContent className="w-full max-w-md">
```

Base primitives (`dialog.jsx`, `alert-dialog.jsx`) already use `w-[calc(100vw-1.5rem)]`. Do not override back to `w-full` on centered dialogs.

## Applies to

- `Dialog` / `AlertDialog` / `CommandDialog` (search, confirm, pickers)
- Custom `DialogPrimitive.Content` centered overlays

## Exceptions (full-width is OK)

- Bottom sheets (`side="bottom"`) and drawers anchored to screen edges
- Side panels (`side="left"` / `side="right"`)
- Full-bleed page routes (e.g. application viewers)

## Also on mobile compact dialogs

- Use `rounded-xl` on the panel
- Prefer horizontal footer buttons for two-action confirms (`flex-row justify-end gap-2`)

See `docs/DESIGN_TEMPLATE.md` §11.1 and §11.9.
